UNITED STATES of America ex rel. August FERNANDEZ, Appellant, v. Benjamin M. DAY, Commissioner of Immigration at the Port of New York, Appellee. No. 417. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 8, 1931. J. Waisman, of New York City, for appellant. Ernest Lappano, of New York City, for appellee.

Before L. HAND, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed on the opinion in United States ex rel. Claussen v. Day, 279 U. S. 398, 49 S. Ct. 354, 73 L. Ed. 758.
